The paper is focused on speech interfaces in HCI, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses natural language processing and speech recognition, which are subfields of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses design and user experience, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SD) or cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also mentions intelligent personal assistants, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
